'''Kafr Thulth''' ({{lang-ar|<U+0643><U+0641><U+0631> <U+062B><U+0644><U+062B>}},  {{lang-he|<U+05DB><U+05E4><U+05E8> <U+05EA>'<U+05D5><U+05DC><U+05EA>}}) is a [[Palestinian]] town located in a height flat land closed to Nablus city and 28 kilometers south of [[Tulkarm]] in the [[Qalqilya Governorate]]. Its average elevation is 270 meters. According to the [[Palestinian Central Bureau of Statistics]], the town had a population of approximately 4,400 inhabitants in mid-year 2006.<ref>[http://www.pcbs.gov.ps/Portals/_pcbs/populati/pop04.aspx Projected Mid -Year Population for Qalqiliya Governorate by Locality  2004- 2006] [[Palestinian Central Bureau of Statistics]]</ref>

It was called (Baalshalisha) before, but the name has been changed to become Kafr Thulth (God of Three).

== Boundries ==
South of [[Azzun]] village , North of Saniria and Bedia villages, from East Diristia village land and West this closed to 1948 lands (green line) and some of Kherab and Aizab separated that belong to Kafr Thulth originally, such as, Salman village, Al-Moudwer, Al-Shaihk Ahmad, Al-Ashqar, Ras Tirah, Al-Dabha, Kirash Kherba, (old place), Ras Atia village .

== Land area ==

The land of it was expanded up to Oja River, it's land include flat land and mountains, it's distance up to 19th century was about fifty <U+2013> six thousand Dunoms, reached up to Hablah village Jaljolya and Saniria <U+2013> Azun and Islah, but this amount of land decreased because of many reasons.
In 1954, the distance was twenty <U+2013> four and nine hundred twenty <U+2013> four Dunoms, while the distance reached up to Kherash Kherba that belong to Kafr Thulth three thousand and six hundred fifty <U+2013> five Dunoms .

== The Second [[Books of Kings]] in its old name ==

4:39 And one went out into the field to gather herbs, and found a wild vine, and gathered thereof wild gourds his lap full, and came and shred them into the pot of pottage: for they knew them not.

4:40 So they poured out for the men to eat. And it came to pass, as they were eating of the pottage, that they cried out, and said, O thou man of God, there is death in the pot. And they could not eat thereof.

4:41 But he said, Then bring meal. And he cast it into the pot; and he said, Pour out for the people, that they may eat. And there was no harm in the pot.

4:42 And there came a man from Baalshalisha, and brought the man of God bread of the firstfruits, twenty loaves of barley, and full ears of corn in the husk thereof. And he said, Give unto the people, that they may eat.

4:43 And his servitor said, What, should I set this before an hundred men? He said again, Give the people, that they may eat: for thus saith the LORD, They shall eat, and shall leave thereof.

== Inhabitants ==

In 1597 was nearly 150 persons. They were about (14 families) but now they are about 5000 persons, but the other kherab and small societies about 4500 persons .

== Lands ==

Kafr Thulth is an old Town three things existed in this town, so there are a lot of places (old one) closed and a round the town mentioned as : -

*Kherbat Kharab :

and it's located in the north direction of the town, and there one water wells, and it's full of places used to put dead persons on its tombs.

*Kherbat Kufr Qari'a:

it's located one kilometer on the east direction, it has a destroyed mosque, cemetery, wells, cajes, pools, refers to romantic regine'(century), and this place was destroyed after misunderstanding with Kafr Thulth people, and this people transfer to Kufr Qaria in Occupied Palestine , this happened in 19th century .

*Kherbat Albaiad: (small and old village) .

It's on the west side of Kufur Thulth about 800 meters distance, it has wells and cafes but it has no ruins, or marks, like Kufur Qari'a. 

*Kherbat Al-Basateen :

it's on southern west of Kafr Thulth, it has wells, and pieces of ruins refers to Romantic period .

*Kherbat Al-Zakoor :

It's located on a height land on west of Kafr Thulth, Jewish kidnap it in 1948, and transfer the inhabitants of  this area, Garaba family was living in this place who the belong to Kufur Thulth, with cafes houses, wells of water, and pools.

*Kherbat Khuraish :

the name of this kherba refers to Sheikh Mohammad Al-Kheerashi, who worked as Imam of Al-Aqsa mosque, and died in 1033 Higri.

*Kherbat Shuhadi :

It's an old place, it's located on the east side of Kafr Thulth within the land of Diristia may be refer to Romantic age, it has water wells and walls .


*Kherbat Abdul Rahim :

It has well and walls, near the old places there is Al-Jamal cafe, it is called Al-Jamal caf<U+00E9>, because there is a statue of kamel, there was a bridegroom loaded on it, and there are some writings on it, pictures, and may  refer to Kanains, many troops have visited Kafr Thulth from Arabs and Foreigners, one of these visitors was Al-Bakri Al-Sideeq who visits Palestine who said going to Kafr Thulth is goodness, and we get in to forest during night and we visited Al-Sheilk Rabee, and with us were many of people (religious people) from sofia.

That means that Kafr Thulth was surrounded with a lot of trees, and a lot of animals dangerous ones, and some of lands and places named by animals like tiger land, oxes village,

== In cccupation == 

This town Kafr Thulth suffered more and more like other cities and villages in Palestine , because of the turkish Age , bad period in 1858 was destroyed because of civil war between Palestinians families and the Fight of posses one of there was Al-Rayan, Al-qassim, and Yamani revolution against Othmany, in rasa, Kafr Thulth was effected Kafr Thulth people they steal there land that owns by farmers, they demand them to pay taxis, Kafr Thulth shared in resistance of Napoleon in 1899, and a French Battalion try to inter  from [[Azzun]]  valley, and it was a safe place for the these replion as Ahmad Al-Tahoni (Abu-Jildi) and Faries Azuni who was the commander of dead platoon, abed Al-Hamed Al-Merdawi Abdul-Kader, Al-Hussani and others, and Kafr Thulth shared in replion movements which moved out of this town for example the repel of Shukher Abu-Kishik and attack molabes, and Faries Al-Azzunai and stand against British Policy, which caused killing of Abdullah Al-Qasas, and others were injured and Kafr Thulth was under curfew eight times, and last for many days. and people crowded in mosque includes children, men and women, and Kafr Thulth people joined 1948 war, 70 people moved to join Iraqi troops near Jaljoliya and Salman Battles near , and sharing in Al-intifadah (uprising) in 1987, and the number of martyrs was about 30 up to 2004.

